  Taq is 832 aa so the above is approximate — get the exact sequence from
  UniProt P19821 (paste the FASTA directly into the app).

  ---
  Note on GFP: It may surprise you — jellyfish live in cold ocean water
  (~15°C) so GFP is genuinely mesophilic, but its fluorescent beta-barrel is
   unusually stable, which might confuse the model the same way myoglobin
  does.
